Male. Protarsomeres 1–3 conspicuously dilated and subbilobed, each covered with modified pale setae ventrally, protarsomere 4 distinctly narrower than preceding ones. Sternite VIII (
Fig. 7
), sternite IX (
Fig. 8
), aedeagus (
